usage: ansi.py [-h] [--alpha ALPHA] [--ansi [COLOR [COLOR ...]]] [--colors]
               [-o {ansi,html}] [-p {16,216,256,bw,grayscale,greyscale}]
               [-t TEXT] [-w WIDTH]
               [file [file ...]]

Images in B/W, Greyscale, 16, 216, and 256 ANSI colors, delivered to STDOUT.
Demo: `curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rupa/ansiimg/master/demo.ansi`

positional arguments:
  file                  image files

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --alpha ALPHA         alpha value for RGBA images (0-255, default 0)
  --ansi [COLOR [COLOR ...]]
                        info for ANSI color (0-255)
  --colors              color cubes
  -o {ansi,html}, --output {ansi,html}
  -p {16,216,256,bw,grayscale,greyscale}, --palette {16,216,256,bw,grayscale,greyscale}
                        palette(s) to use
  -t TEXT, --text TEXT  (short) text to overlay
  -w WIDTH, --width WIDTH
                        default is terminal width (80)
